  "prompt": "Can a Guitar Hero guitar be used in Rock Band?",
  "response": "Yes, a Guitar Hero guitar can generally be used with Rock Band, but compatibility depends on the specific console and generation of the games you are using. Here\u2019s a general overview:\n\n- **Xbox 360**: Guitar Hero guitars typically work with Rock Band games. Compatibility is quite good across most games on this platform.\n\n- **PlayStation 3**: Guitar Hero guitars are generally compatible with Rock Band games, although there may be some exceptions or specific models that have connectivity issues.\n\n- **Wii**: Compatibility can be more hit-or-miss. Some Guitar Hero guitars work with Rock Band games, but not all models are guaranteed to be compatible.\n\n- **Newer Consoles (Xbox One, PlayStation 4, etc.)**: Compatibility tends to be more limited. Harmonix and Activision have released specific adapters and models that may work, so checking specific compatibility lists from these companies for newer systems is advised.\n\nIf you are looking to use a Guitar Hero guitar with a Rock Band game, it's recommended to verify compatibility for your specific console and versions of the games. Checking online forums, official compatibility charts, or the websites of the game's developers can also provide helpful information.",
